1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f6e0c0;strokeColor=#c9932a;fontColor=#5a3f10;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="2394" y="70" width="280" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Future humans count&lt;br&gt;(discounted)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;   24 lives-eq/$1k · 80% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Rainforest Trust · 18%&lt;br&gt;▼ 19 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + nature_intrinsic_value + climate_tipping_points + future_humans_matter_with_discounting&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Future people are inside the circle, but with a positive pure-time discount rate — the moderate longtermist position. A modest discount is enough to keep present, measurable global health competitive with future-protecting work; remove it (the next assumption) and the astronomical numbers take over. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 nature_intrinsic_value → 4 climate_tipping_points → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_3_4_5.drawio" id="w1_2_3_4_5"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f5d3b8;strokeColor=#cc7a33;fontColor=#5a300e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="2467" y="415" width="280" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+7]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;   21k lives-eq/$1k · 71% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Wild insects (humane pesticides) · 29%&lt;br&gt;(Bob Fischer, Brian Tomasik)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + nature_intrinsic_value + climate_tipping_points + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 nature_intrinsic_value → 4 climate_tipping_points → 7 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWG1v2koW%2FitH0d5dyAIx5i3Q7UppXm6rJm2UpoqumooO9gCzsT3eGRNKe3t%2F%2Bz4zY4MpzhYpX1pizzznOe%2Fn%2BPtByKdsEWWnMuQHo4OjI3r58iXdKiYSyiQFin1b4ccyofuF77W7tJQqCh8FX9KyPfbHnXF3PKCazmRKg7q5fJ8A5ETrRZxmQiYUzIE1Io9SpmQwFywyUO2hT22aMjVmS7YazxcxS3TxwieWiJhFeqxlzJdzlhVvOpSwbKH4WCSZEokWwfiRRQtevO9SEOFmxseZSFORzMapxNE18mCNjEMZh%2FRxJDNL%2BZwFc2Ib3kITo%2BtVNsfvqYg4wSKb1%2FqIMsOLhaFukOIwo0i4JqksmOJNqMtiDhlC43k2584S%2F9A0XSSBxXhBgYxTqcFzcwB3k5ADEY%2BEtmg6Y0nIIplwiuGnqEVf1m44f%2FxiqJrr%2FGvKgwwXnUnk1CJsPNayYK%2B4zmiyWNHCiDEXNS8rNqIPcyXilO54BP9wulbyP8B1t38%2Ff3d%2Bc3J7fkaTFc14whWM3UpXRXjwUGRbZjrEywYlMnNkjCWBZLE%2BJgFXmVE5lgphsbaYdmedOViaRoLrFn1Yxa1IzhKp4MDa97TXoHTY%2B1G3WNZbQ%2B83On3zwp6c8Iy5p6mSEzYRkchAZCKN2qGJ7U9eg9qfW3TBgkxCJnR1UDiQGh8kWYO0JG4CQ6oZPHf%2BaXl2cvnH0d8%2B04RHcokANneth%2FlX%2FI5WuA5sWNViQXa4CDLnC3iPI8qhvgviO%2Fh0dc3Va1jXGPrlrorIm5bXtoqOyP9RJwKo5dDk%2F10IOBosKYUf5zkIJGY2CkYwetKMmXrgGcgJnXHYu%2Bli44jubq9pKnEPpskYNA1k8gh3ONtYEVQLlNS6GQD7Ac%2FhccUfOWSGxJNHoWQSQzyLmrF85OYnaRYoMRUBh1eAjlC7dXl4KicIlimCo1LLQsVurmKexSDVLO4hDde6UaZkKgLEjBMyopOYfcOJUPAJCx6c4%2FMSQDyy5Kwz2dpQKALS5IFeC0M9WSgGI90n%2BaMz56DbQPpPesfzc%2B74veUh65bs9L0PWc6yI3oFtjrCc0Q8DIeQhIraxkfA1AQa1P7qt455s0M20LI6%2FZOu37wFN5QKWyGShEdUeyuzb0eX8Aa4JMnRHU%2B%2B0V%2Ft4W%2FGSb7XHTYITJvFrcK18EpulGtTFq9Q%2BIXJLvX%2FvdLP1crvNm1NJRbjKnzNbLmc8JVMQtKxlNmcQhazGZKidiODB52p%2B4XnTfuxSz%2BmkM8v6ETFeCPhoKvgLVsRwpShtPme78MYOmAh1%2FW8VJwJBbcRn07NfxBXSsoU1YqpFblACQR%2BN%2BjV%2BcX7m3NXWCzCkovZPAP7BsoTwiCWJia