farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 nature_intrinsic_value → 4 climate_tipping_points → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 8 suffering_focused → 9 meat_eater_problem → 10 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJytWW1v2zgS%2FiuD4PbOztqOJL%2BnlwPSxNkWTdog9V6waAqXlmibG4nUkVJct9v97TckJVlOlI0Ovg8NVIl85pn3If39IKALkobJmQjowfHB0RGcnJzAVBLGIRHgS%2FJtgw9rDnep57g9WAsZBg%2BMrmHtzrxZd9abDWej2XjmOtBQiYjBdZoa5I4j2KlSaRQnTHDwV4h5DA7ERAp%2FxUioId2xBy4siJyRNdnMVmlEuMo%2FeEA4i0ioZkpEdL0iSf6lC5wkqaQzxhPJuGL%2B7IGEKc2%2F98APcWdCZwmLY8aXs1jg0gJ5WCDjooSi9FkoCvQRqHSxoFLvWwg%2FVTTIP40hoiSZ4T%2FcFEsxD2lU6OEAp8mM0yVJ2AOdWRGzEJ%2BVscaE%2BCsgW5MwBQSuN8kKnxcspIBG335WR5BolUkQqBZIip5inCoQ0oBJ2kZLkogiE6bwfbKi1sj%2FULBIuW8wXoEvolgoVGW7APfygCIivmKWmkoID0goOIUIQyHswJfC05OHL5qq3k6%2FxtRPcKO1tlgYhG1QdAzYa6oSmKcbSLUYvVHRsmLH8HElWRTDLQ3R9RSupfgdce3uXybvJzen08k5zDewpJxKNHYn3uQRSAOW7JjpED%2B2gKP%2FDBltSUQyWL9yn8pEqxwJiRFXWEzZtdYcJI5DRlUHPm6iTiiWXEh0XON73G9BPO7%2FaBos462x8xOcvX1lVs5pQuxbHQhkzkKWIJG50GoHOn0%2BOS1wP3fggviJQJmoq4XCBbH2AU9aoARQHRhCLtFzk0%2Fr89PL347%2B9hnmNBRrzA2913iYfsXncIPbERutarBQdpD6ifUF1eHJFaq%2FCEWKu1bo%2BHOmfOSUwMlTBTEhO87IqKkfRz%2BaACa4EBN1WFO2XCE2pq%2FEmNdRtCI6oahS0JiKiCh2%2Fwr%2BjQrpb57jOWisInuuJUPqyaZasttxM8GDTj8TTL8mkpTEkgf0n4ZGnSnHMCqwnxdvS8MthvPmmso3GFg6xp5TPufgZQyM%2Bdv0