ls)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+9]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;   24 lives-eq/$1k · 83% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Rainforest Trust · 16%&lt;br&gt;(Michael Dickens, Vasco Grilo)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + nature_intrinsic_value + climate_tipping_points + meat_eater_problem&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The meat-eater problem: a dollar of human global health also buys decades of that person&#x27;s meat consumption, and factory farming it causes suffering the animal circle now counts. Each present-human org is charged an additive penalty — farmed-animal life-years caused per human DALY, times the suffering per factory-farmed life-year, times the animal&#x27;s welfare range. Under a heavy animal welfare range the penalty can exceed the human benefit, so saving human lives looks net-harmful. Only bites once animals count, so it requires animals_somewhat; and it is a near-term human-vs-animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans), where x-risk dominates and the meat bookkeeping is moot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 nature_intrinsic_value → 4 climate_tipping_points → 9 meat_eater_problem" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWGtv2zgW%2FSsXwc6unbUdSX67mwXSPKZBkzZIUxSDpnBpiba5kUQtKcd1O53fvoeUZMuNuhWQD0kUiTz33Cfv5beDgM%2FZKkxPZcAPJgdHR3R8fEx3iomYUkm%2BYl83eFjHdL%2FyHLdHa6nC4FHwNa3dqTftTnvTMTV0KhMaN83m%2BxggJ1qvoiQVMiZ%2FCawJOZQwJf2lYKGBcsceuTRnasrWbDNdriIW6%2BKDRywWEQv1VMuIr5csLb50KWbpSvGpiFMlYi386SMLV7z43iM%2FxM6UT1ORJCJeTBOJpVvkMUWcpVP8cDVNlJyFPLKEz5m%2FJLZjLTQxutmkSzzPRcgJ9th91keUGlYsCHSLFIcRRcw1SWXBFG9DWRZxSBEa79Mlz%2BzwD03zVexbjBfkyyiRGix3C7A3DjgQ8Upoi6ZTFgcslDGnCF4KO%2FR564Tzx8%2BGqtnOvyTcT7ExM4icW4SdvzoW7CXXKc1WG1oZMWaj5mXFJnQHrFfGHZyuOFuseLbx9%2FM357cnd%2BdnNNvQgsdcwYadZFPEBQ9EumehQ3xsUSzTjIcxIpAs1vvY5yo12kZSIR62xtLZ2swSLElCwXWH3m2iTigXsVSIica3pN%2BiZNz%2F3rRY1lFj5zc6vXxhV854yrK3xr9sJkKRgshMGo0DE9QfnRa5nzp0wfxU